<br>
One quest many have done and that you could start on (and gain xp/faction at the same time), is the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest.  The beginning of this quest is at:  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=937">Cloth Coldain Prayer Shawl</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Getting the toes and heads should provide you some ample entertainment when you get up to early 30's.  Plus as you level you'll be able to further yourself on this quest all the way up to the 8th (not a light undertaking). <br>
<br>
Way back when they were released, the quests in the Temple of Solusek Ro (just off of Lavastorm) were great rewards for the levels intended.  Consequently, the mage focus items are quests here.  I'm not sure if these other quests were mentioned above, but here goes:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=708">Robe of the Elements</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1763">Earthen Boots</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
You can also go kill Evil Eyes in the Beholder's Maze and grab you a couple of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=785"><br>
Polished Bone Bracers</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  <br>
<br>
And if you have just a little plat (150-200) you can buy a Stein of Maggok (sorry, I couldn't find on Allakhazam offhand and am not a premium member so can't search it out).  The stein is GREAT for lower/mid levels as it has 10 int and some other stats (primary slot).  You'd be surprised at how many of these are around :-)<br>
<br>
And one more note--while intelligent is great to start working on, the very best you can do for your level is get as much pure mana as possible.  I'm not sure of the exact formula, but you're not getting *much* mana per point of int.  I'm not saying don't get int items, but try to take a look at some of the pure mana items out there as well.  If you manage to get over 200 int, I don't think it helps much (maybe 1 mana/int) until you pass level 50.  Keep that in mind, and happy hunting :-)<br>
